title: The Surrogate
description: A boy is brought in and he calls his father to come. He offers to donate blood if he needs it. But tests reveal the man is not the boy's father. He tells them he found him a few years ago and took him in. And he eventually would think of him as his son. Trapper tells the authorities and they learns that the boy ran away from his mother. When she comes he doesn't want to be with her. But the man doesn't have any rights so he tells him he has to go with her. And he becomes catatonic.

title: Have You Hugged Your Nurse Today?
Warning: I May Be Hazardous to Your Health
'Til Life Do Us Part
description: A patient who is diagnosed with a serious form of cancer finds inspiration in a woman with Lou Gehrig's disease.

title: If You Can't Stand the Heat
Strike!
description: A possible nurse's strike threatens the hospital as well as Gonzo's love life.

title: It's a Wise Surgeon
description: Gonzo is suspicious of a young Korean man who comes to the hospital claiming to be the long-lost son of Trapper. A woman with a history of faking illness is surprised when she is diagnosed with a rare disease.

title: Short Odds
description: Gonzo tries to date a new surgeon who suffers a loss of confidence after her first patient dies.

title: Quarantine
description: Trapper's ex-wife Melanie finds a baby in a fitting room and the hospital is put at risk when the baby is found to have a form of the plague.

title: Hot Line
description: Gonzo and the staff decide to start a hot-line for people to anonymously call with their problems. Trapper takes a risk by bringing in a retired doctor with an alcohol problem to help perform a rare eye operation.

title: Girl Under Glass: Part 1
description: A controlling millionaire publisher gives the hospital a large donation in exchange for Gonzo watching over his daughter who has a rare blood disorder that needs round-the-clock care and is smitten with Dr. Gates. Trapper must find a replacement for Starch who has gotten married and retired.

title: Girl Under Glass: Part 2
description: With Gonzo accused of sexual misconduct, the hospital faces a public relations nightmare.

title: Slim Chance
description: When Gonzo learns that an old classmate has put her health and sanity at risk by following a strict diet which encourages the use of diuretics, he goes after the well-respected doctor who founded the diet.

title: Call Me Irresponsible
description: Riverside comes under fire after he takes over one of Gonzo's patients who happens to be dating his father and she ends up almost dying from an allergic reaction to fluorine.

title: Creepy Time Gal
description: Gonzo and Trapper are unsure how to treat a college student who has gotten mysteriously sick while doing a research paper on satanic rituals.

title: Straight and Narrow
description: When a cop who is found to be homosexual is shot at a gay rally, Gonzo believes that he may have been shot by someone on the force and may be in danger at the hospital.

title: Earthquake
description: Trapper and Gonzo go on a trip to a cabin which becomes an adventure when an earthquake hits and the woman staying at the cabin needs serious medical care. At the hospital, Riverside leads the evacuation when the earthquake hits.

title: The Pagoda Cure
description: Members of the staff are baffled when a Vietnamese woman, who had initially refused surgery, is mysteriously operated on overnight without anyone seeing it. Trapper recognizes a politician who checks in under a false name and is brought in by a younger woman that is not his wife.

title: Have I Got a Girl for You
description: A shy and clumsy nurse asks Trapper for advice on how to attract Gonzo. A woman who is obsessed with her appearance is reluctant to have a tumor in her face removed.

title: Who's the Lucky Father?
description: A noted con man believes that the hospital is trying to pull one over on him when he is told that he needs a life-saving operation and his girlfriend is pregnant.

title: Finders Keepers
description: Gonzo and Trapper try to track down the family of a 10-year old girl who was hit by a car and is exhibiting erratic behavior. The only leads they have are gang members with whom she was living with.

title: Days of Wine and Leo
description: Trapper convinces the board to fill the position of diagnosing physician with a former war buddy who is a double amputee.

title: A Case of the Crazies
description: There is plenty of excitement at the hospital for the opening of the day care center. However, the excitement is short-lived when a child is injured in a fall and it is found out that the day care director was once in a mental institution.

title: Second Sight
description: Instead of using his spare time to study for his medical boards, Jackpot looks into a sight restoring operation for his blind girlfriend.

title: Hate Is Enough
description: A man is brought in who claims to be writing a book on the KKK. Later someone comes and sees him and threatens him. When Gonzo tries to talk to him about what he said, he denies it. Later Gonzo finds in his things that he's telling the truth and that one of the hospital's brilliant doctors is the head.

title: Is There a Doctor in the Big House?
It Only Hurts When I Love
I Only Have Ice for You
What a Difference a Day Makes
The Final Cut
description: Gonzo has been training three doctors for cardiac surgery. But he is told due to budget reasons, he has to cut one of them. So he sets out to do that by getting to know them personally.

title: My Son the Doctor
description: When Trapper's son J.T. a recent medical school graduate who's a bit of a delinquent gets in trouble which causes him to lose the job he was hoping to get. So Trapper reluctantly gives him a job at the hospital and he continues to act immature.

title: School Nurse
description: When a friend of Shoop's a nurse at a public school is attacked and when the police tell her no one is willing to come forward to say who her attacker is. She goes and fills in for her friend so that she could find the attacker. And the detective assigned to the case is telling her to be careful. And eventually her work at the hospital starts to suffer.

title: Double Bubble
description: A young boy is brought to the hospital, needing a transplant from a close relative. They discover that his father is a reclusive millionaire. J.T. calls his office and is taken to his home where he tries to implore the man to help his son.

title: Buckaroo Bob Rides Again
description: An actor who played a popular character on television is brought to the hospital and everybody id pleased to see him. Later he's informed by the company that owns the rights to the character he played is telling him to cease appearing as him. Also his old co-star who's now a successful businessman who didn't like being the butt of the joke comes to see him and tells him he's glad that when the show was canceled. And the man is left with nothing.

title: In the Eyes of the Beholder
All the King's Horses...
description: Trapper and J.T. go to Tahow for a little R & R. While there a girl falls into a frozen lake, J.T. saves her and she is brought to the hospital. but she's in a coma. Her uncle, a very outspoken TV personality, is upset that they either are responsible for his niece's condition or are not doing all they can. So he goes on his show attacking them.

title: Go for Broker
description: One of the hospital's doctors brings a mail order bride from the Philippines.

title: The Second Best Man
description: Melanie's about to get married. But she's getting anonymous love notes. She assumes it's Trapper but it's not.

title: Billboard Barney
description: A Little League outfielder chasing a fly ball gets a whiff of what's beyond the fence -- and collapses. He's been poisoned by a chemical spill from a pipeline just beyond the fence which is carrying illegal toxic chemicals. The boy's father chains himself to a company billboard to get attention to the company's policies.

title: Going, Going, Gonzo
description: Gregory Harrison's last episode is a tour de force for him (presumably he was lured back for the seventh season with the promise of a big exit show) as surgeon "Gonzo" Gates, who suffers a major stroke while walking in a hospital corridor. He lives, but his mobility, speech and cognitive skills are severely impaired. His bride Fran (who has multiple sclerosis) and his group at the hospital try to help him rehabilitate and succeed to a degree, but he goes on a permanent vacation to try to see what he wants to do if he can no longer operate.

title: Judgement Day
description: When a doctor who is a friend of Jackpot's is dying and she appears to have given up any hope and wants to die. She goes to court asking that she be allowed to die. And the judge presiding over the case is Jackpot's estranged father.

title: Research and Destroy
description: The hospital is besieged by protesters. They appear to be targeting a particular doctor who performed dangerous and unauthorized experiments in the past.
